tion%20expanded%20its%20focus%2C%20addressing%20not%20only%20women%E2%80%99s%20health%20but%20also%20the%20societal%20structures%20that%20perpetuate%20inequities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20collaborated%20with%20various%20organisations%20dedicated%20to%20women%E2%80%99s%20empowerment%2C%20both%20nationally%20and%20internationally%2C%20establishing%20her%20identity%20through%20her%20impactful%20work.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Kalpana%2C%20her%20marriage%20was%20liberating.%20She%20continues%20to%20lead%20with%20empathy%2C%20shaped%20by%20her%20partnership%20and%20her%20personal%20journey.%20Her%20story%20is%20a%20poignant%20reminder%20that%20liberation%20can%20take%20many%20forms%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20even%20in%20the%20shadow%20of%20grief%2C%20women%20can%20redefine%20what%20it%20means%20to%20lead%2C%20resist%20and%20transform.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EClimate%20vulnerabilities%20intertwined%20with%20gender-based%20violence%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdst.gov.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FFull%2520Report%2520%25281%2529.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EClimate%20Vulnerability%20Assessment%20for%20Adaptation%20Planning%20in%20India%20Using%20a%20Common%20Framework%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20fourteen%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20most%20climate-vulnerable%20districts%20are%20in%20Bihar%2C%20including%20Madhubani.%20Communities%20in%20Madhubani%20and%20Supaul%20districts%20face%20extreme%20vulnerability%20due%20to%20climate%2C%20geographical%2C%20and%20socio-economic%20factors.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFloods%20during%20monsoons%2C%20driven%20by%20the%20proximity%20to%20the%20Kosi%20River%2C%20devastate%20agriculture%20%E2%80%94%20the%20primary%20livelihood%20%E2%80%94%20pushing%20families%20into%20poverty.%20This%20economic%20instability%20often%20exacerbates%20social%20issues%2C%20including%20school%20dropouts